    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The cmake build scripts are meant mostly for:\r\n- be able to build on Windows (where cmake is our primary build system).\r\n- to be able to integrate well with cmake based projects on other platforms (cmake is not our primary build system on Linux and Mac).\r\n\r\nIf you are needing the pkgconfig files, why don't you just install using `make install` (not using cmake at all)? The cmake-based install is there mostly to provide a gRPCConfig.cmake so that other cmake based project can include gRPC using find_package().  So I am not sure if duplicating the pkgconfig files installation makes sense."
  },
